    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wooden discs in which figures have been applied in high relief that depict proverbs and sayings. They are mainly used to discuss a disagreement between spouses or to advise children. This custom is mainly found among the Bantu people of Central Africa.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
